{
  "texts": [
    "Here, the function, k(t), describes the filter of the voltage response to a current pulse.",
    "Input current I(t) is filtered with a filter k(t) and produces corresponding input potential hðtÞ ¼ R 1 0 kðsÞIðt À sÞds.",
    "A spike occurs when the membrane potential, u(t), reaches the threshold v th (t).",
    "The membrane potential after a spike is described by a function η(t).",
    "The function, η(t) models the refractory behavior after a spike."
  ]
}